At least five people were injured after a light delivery truck and a light motor vehicle collided head-on with each other on Broadway Road in Durban, paramedics said on Friday. Netcare911 paramedics said they worked alongside another emergency service on scene. A father and a son from the light motor vehicle were treated and transported by paramedics from the other service, paramedics did assist to treat the patients. The other three men who were the occupants of the light delivery truck were assessed by paramedics and transported privately to a nearby hospital, said Netcare911. The accident happened on Friday at about 13h00. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.